      "type": "abstract",
      "value": "Robert Kilburn Root's 1910 selection prints the four anonymous Middle English verse works that conclude Princeton Garrett MS 143. The first narrates Saint Gregory's trental and the release of his mother from purgatory; the following refrain lyrics counsel charitable speech, gratitude to God in adversity, and penitential amendment before death. Root's edition preserves scribal errors, adds punctuation, expands contractions in italics, and supplies stanza spacing for the final three lyrics.",
