      "value": "Four numbered poem units on printed pp. 365-379 contain 522 encoded verse lines: The Trental of St Gregory, 258 lines; All Way Fond to Say the Best, 80 lines in ten stanzas; Thank God of All, 88 lines in eleven stanzas; and For Thy Sins Amends Make, 96 lines in twelve stanzas. They occupy current manuscript fols. 38v-51v and Princeton IIIF canvases 84-110.",
